  "texts": [
    "Most importantly, further research is needed on how to interpret user signals during the interaction in relation to the evolving explanation.",
    "Interpreting users' speech, gestures, facial expressions, signals of doubt etc.",
    "is key to understanding whether the current explanation satisfies their needs and provides a basis for adapting appropriately.",
    "An open question here would also be how to implement a reasoning component that can deduce information needs from what the user says, and that can recognize knowledge gaps effectively.",
    "This will let the system decide how an explanation is to be adapted to meet the user's needs and close knowledge gaps."
  ],
